DIARRHEA, FATAL, UNDIAGNOSED - NEPAL
************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 1998 12:32:54 -0500
From: Michael Peat <MIKE@inside-us.com>
Source: June 4th issue of the Katmandu Post, Bengal

Dolkha toll reaches 15.
DOLKHA, June 3 (PR) - The death toll from diarrhoea in Dolkha district has
shot up to 15 in Dolkha as fresh news of 8 more deaths has arrived.
Earlier, seven persons have died of the same disease last week.
Chief of District Public Health Office Asta Ratna Tuladhar said that a
medical team has left for Lamabagar. "The disease has come under control,"
he said.
Other team has left for Jhyarmu and Gauri Shanker too, as the news broke
that the diarrhoea has attacked the people there too, Tuladhar added.
--
Michael Peat
Director of Technology
INISIDE Technology USA, Inc.
e-mail: MIKE@inside-us.com
[Fatal diarrhea is often either cholera -- watery diarrhea, or dysentery --
bloody diarrhea due to _Shigella_. Can any of our subscribers in Nepal
tell us which kind this is? - Mod.JW]
